    <note>Xu(4) Zhongrong [7244] His ancestors were Jingzhao people. His family moved to Suzhou, Wuxian. Generational names, Shen(2) Gua's [1450] authorship of the funerary inscriptions for the son and daughter of Xu(4) Shi [18653], son of Zhongzhuang [18652], and chronological logic make it almost certain that Zhongrong was a son of Yanzuo [18651], who first settled in Wuxian. Shen(2) Zhou's [7323] father-in-law. YLDD, 2367.9b. CBD, 3, 2176.</note>
